Time Limit: 1 sec
Memory: 256 MB

Description
Given two numbers N and M and a 2D array of size N × M. For each row, print the inverted array that appears in the mirror (i.e., reverse the elements of each row).

Input Format
The first line contains an integer T, the number of test cases.
For each test case:
The first line contains two space-separated integers N and M.
Then N lines follow, each containing M space-separated integers, representing the elements of the array.

Output Format
For each test case, print the inverted array.
Specifically, for each row, print the elements in reverse order, with each row's elements printed on a new line, separated by spaces.

Constraints
1 ≤ T ≤ 10
1 ≤ N, M ≤ 100
1 ≤ A[i][j] ≤ 10⁹

Sample Input 1
1
3 3
2 3 5
7 9 20
35 1 12

Sample Output 1
5 3 2
20 9 7
12 1 35

Note

For the given array:

2 3 5
7 9 20
35 1 12

After reversing each row, the array becomes:

5 3 2
20 9 7
12 1 35

We mirror each row by reversing the elements.


#include<iostream>
typedef long long ll;
#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;


int main()
{
    int t;
    cin>>t;
    while(t--)
    {
        int n,m;
        cin>>n>>m;
        vector<vector<int>>v(n,vector<int>(m));
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
        {
            for(int j = 0; j < m; j++)
            {
                cin>>v[i][j];
            }
        }
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
        {
            reverse(v[i].begin(),v[i].end());
        } 
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
        {
            for(int j = 0; j < m; j++)
            {
                cout<<v[i][j]<<" ";
            }
            cout<<endl;
        }

      
        
    }
}
